The above posting included the following information: "France has recorded
a total of 15 cases of the human form of the disease, variant
Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease, since it 1st appeared in 1996".
The following data are derived from the official website of the European
and allied countries collaborative study group of CJD (EUROCJD), at
<http://www.eurocjd.ed.ac.uk/vcjdworldeuro.htm>http://www.eurocjd.ed.ac.uk/vcjdworldeuro.htm>
variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease
current data as of August 2006
total cases (number alive)
France 20 (3)
