[2]
Date: Thu 12 Oct 2006
From: "CAPEK Isabelle" <i.capek@invs.sante.fr>

This posting from Ms Christina Foster mentions that France has 15 human
cases of the human form of the disease, variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease,
since it first appeared in 1996.
I would like to provide more recent information. France has recorded 21
cases of definite and probable variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease since
1996, including 3 cases still alive.
Reports are published monthly by the National Institute for Public Health
Surveillance (Institut de Veille Sanitaire) at
<http://www.invs.sante.fr/publications/mcj/donnees_mcj.html>.
--
Dr Isabelle CAPEK
Epidemiologiste
Departement maladies infectieuses
Unite maladies enteriques, alimentaires et zoonoses Institut de veille
sanitaire
12 rue du Val d'Osne
94415 Saint-Maurice Cedex
email: <i.capek@invs.sante.fr>
[We are grateful to these readers for updating the number of vCJD cases in
France, correcting the information included in the cited AFP newswire. -
Mod.AS]
